      <title>Alex Fedorov</title>
      <link>https://cedwards57.github.io/webtest/posts/team/phd/alex-fedorov/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 11 Nov 2022 05:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://cedwards57.github.io/webtest/posts/team/phd/alex-fedorov/</guid>
      <description>Research Summary I am interested in the following topics (with selected works):
Self-Supervision: Natural Images [ICLR 2019], Neuroimaging [IEEE BHI 2019][MICCAI 2020][NeurIPS ML4H Workshop 2019] Multimodal Learning: Neuroimaging [IEEE ICHI 2021] Out-of-distribution Generalization, Robustness and Fairness: Neuroimaging [ICLR RobustML Workshop 2021] Interpretability: Neuroimaging [IEEE ISBI 2021], [Preprint] Image Segmentation: Brain Tissue [IJCNN 2017], Atlas [BigNeuro Workshop NeurIPS 2017] I also worked on Reinforcement Learning [NeurIPS Deep RL Workshop 2015] and Computer Vision problems (traffic sign recognition; age and gender recognition from human faces).</description>
    </item>
    
